  "prompt": "Is the driver job in Uber considered as work experience when applying for higher studies abroad?",
  "response": "The consideration of Uber driver experience as work experience for higher studies abroad depends on several factors:\n\n1. Academic Program\n- Some programs may value practical experience\n- Technical or business-related courses might consider it more favorably\n- Depends on the specific university and program requirements\n\n2. Overall Application\n- Part of a broader work experience profile\n- May be considered if you demonstrate skills like:\n  - Customer service\n  - Time management\n  - Problem-solving\n  - Entrepreneurial spirit\n\n3. Additional Factors\n- Duration of work\n- Supplementary roles or responsibilities\n- How you present the experience in your application\n- Relevance to the chosen field of study\n\n4. Recommendation\n- Highlight transferable skills\n- Explain how driving experience contributed to personal/professional growth\n- Provide context and specific examples\n- Use it as a supplementary part of your work experience\n\n5. Variations by Country/University\n- Different academic systems have different perspectives\n- Some are more open to diverse work experiences\n- Research specific university requirements\n\nWhile Uber driving might not be considered traditional work experience, presenting it thoughtfully can potentially add value to your application.",
